			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Ok does anyone like this idea?
<br />

<br />
Since our first studies began, mages have sought to master all things being elemental. Once a Magician reaches the Elemental Planes they can use this Elemental Mastery channeled thru their Orb of Mastery to begin to meld all things elemental. With this melding ability comes the opportunity to magnify each elementals innate properties to benefit different situations and enemies of the Magician.
<br />

<br />
As a Magician enters the Elemental Planes an aura of energy surges within the Magician and their very being evolves to a new level of insight, knowledge, and spellcasting abilities. Their pets, schools of magic , mana regenerating, and spell power are forever changed as their elemental mastery is now combined with the essence of the gods. 
<br />

<br />
For example:
<br />

<br />
Pets gain the advantages of the Elemental Planes as follows:
<br />

<br />
1) A Bejeweled Pet[Earth]-> is now summoned, this pet has all the normal charactistics of an Earth pet but is native to the plane of Earth. Combined of earth, gems, blue diamonds, quartz and mithryl this colossal elemental is the purest form of Rathe. It's two eyes gleam with inner fires, and it's huge fists and feet bristle with jagged shards.  A bejeweled elemental is not particularly swift but is tremendously strong. With its outstretched fists/feet it can crush and tear its opponents. It is also content to simply overrun an enemy if it can. Its crystalline/mineral form gives it formidable armor and allows it to resist damage, even when dealt with spells and magic weapons. It has Root, Rend[tears apart its opponent with its fists], Slam, Trample[against small or large only] and Sluggish[its natural attacks are treated as a slow weapon] abilities. It has the ability to Dual Wield and because of its strength, Bejeweled elementals get 1/5 times their strength bonus to damage on their primary slam attacks, although they only get half the strength bonus with their off-hand attacks. This pet is immune to poison, disease and fire attacks
<br />

<br />
2) Steam Elemental[Air/Fire]-> This pet is created by the advanced magician who can meld air and fire. This pet has all the normal charactistics of an Air pet. this pet has all the normal charactistics of an Air pet. A Steam elemental is an extremely powerful super heated creature. This maelstrom of super heated air actually causes winds to manifest around its opponent creating a knockback and swirl attack. It has all the advantages of a normal air pet, plus Blow Away[whirl till you hurl], Scalding Rush[moves over an opponent and causes it to become scalded], Damage Shield, Air Elemental Strike[a blast that buffets, stuns and knockbacks an enemy] Breathless [sucks the air out of an enemy's lungs causing its natural defense to become lowered]
<br />
This pet is immune to fire and magic attacks.
<br />

<br />

<br />
3) Tempest Elemental[Water/Air]-> This pet is created by the advanced magician who can meld water and air. this pet has all the normal charactistics of a Water pet. A Tempest elemental appears as a water elemental gliding on tumultous blankets of extremely cold numbing air and unseen winds. Soaring in to ambush foes with terrible speed this elemental attacks from behind with numbing daggers of ice. This pet has all the advantages of a normal water pet, plus Ice Storm [a rain of ice daggers] , Frozen Death Grip[An ice encasing/entombing temp efftect] and Shield of Frost[a DS of Ice] This pet is immune to magic and cold attacks.
<br />

<br />
4) Lava Elemental[Fire/Earth]-> This pet is created by the advanced magician who can meld fire and earth. This pet has all the normal charactistics of a fire pet. A lava elemental appears like a surging mound of molten rock, It is more deliberate than its pure fire kin but just as dedicated to destruction. A lava Elemental is nearly as powerful as a Bejeweled elemental but also benefits from a firery nature. It is very straight forward in combat, confident that most opponents cannot stand long against its mighty blows and all-consuming heat. Lava Splash [this attack procs a scorching effect in the form of a splash of lava. All creatures within 10 feet are effected by this effect], Lava aura[A Damage Shield], Pyroclastic Cloud[This volcanic cloud made of molten rock and superheated gases simply incinerates all targeted enemies in its path. This pet is immune to fire, poision and disease attacks.
<br />

<br />
The effects of reaching the elemental planes can also provide changes to schools of magic , mana regenerating, and spell casting abilities.
<br />

<br />

<br />
Just an idea!<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=639739" target="_blank" class="postlink">Danille Impholder</a>
<br />
Ayonae Ro, Lost Fires
<br />
Death Before Dishonor</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
